                <note resp="Philip Lampi">"To the Freemen of the Fourth electoral district.  Fellow Citizens, The time is not for distant, when you will be called on to appoint an elector to vote for President and Vice President of the United States.  For that appointment I am a candidate and should I be honored with your suffrages shall vote for James Madison, President--for Vice President undetermined. William Martin, Smith County, May 15 [1808]."  The Clarion (Nashville, TN).  April 26, 1808.</note>
